Both outputs written.

- **transcript.json** (63 KB): 25 iterations, 99 hypotheses, 99 analyses, schema-conformant. dataset_id=`ds001_breast`, model_id=`claude-opus-4-7`, harness_id=`manual-claude-code@2026-04-27`, max_iterations=25.
- **analysis_summary.txt** (13 KB): Narrative walkthrough of all 14 thematic blocks of analyses with directions, magnitudes, p-values, supported-vs-refuted verdicts, and overall conclusions.

Headline findings:
- **Palbociclib × ER+** is the single dominant precision-medicine signal (+1.58 mo, p≈0; survives full multivariable adjustment). PIK3CA mutation strongly attenuates this benefit (interaction = -2.34, p≈0).
- Olaparib × BRCA1/2 shows a marginal positive interaction (+0.4 mo, p=0.02) that does not survive adjustment.
- Trastuzumab/HER2, sacituzumab/HER2-low or TNBC, pembrolizumab/MSI-high or TNBC, and tamoxifen/ER show **no** selective benefit.
- Strong prognostic features: ECOG, stage IV, brain mets, albumin, weight loss, Ki-67, HER2+, PIK3CA. Age has an inverted (positive) PFS slope.
- Null: comorbidities, symptom grades, SNPs (after Bonferroni), race/insurance/rural/education, sex, most mets sites.
